🚀 Prompt-a-thon 2026
(Part of AI Premier League 2026)
🔍 What is Prompt-a-thon?

Prompt-a-thon is a hands-on learning challenge designed to help employees effectively use AI tools like ChatGPT and GitHub Copilot in their daily work.

Participants will learn how to:

Write effective prompts
Solve real work problems using AI
Improve productivity across development, testing, analysis, and reporting

👉 This is a beginner-friendly event — no prior AI experience required.

🎯 Objectives
Enable teams to use AI effectively in daily tasks
Build foundational skills in prompt engineering
Identify practical AI use cases across roles
Create a shared prompt library for the organization
👥 Who Can Participate?

Open to all roles:

Developers
Testers / QA
Business Analysts
Project / Delivery Managers

Team Size: 3–5 members
(Cross-functional teams encouraged)

🧩 What is Expected from Participants?

Each team should:

Identify a real work problem
Use AI tools to solve it using effective prompts
Create a set of 5–10 high-quality prompts
Demonstrate:
Input → AI output
Improvement in effort or quality
💡 Sample Use Cases
👨‍💻 Developers
Generate unit tests
Refactor code
Debug errors
🧪 Testers
Generate test cases
Create test data
Improve bug reports
📊 Business Analysts
Convert requirements to user stories
Summarize documents
Create acceptance criteria
📈 Managers
Generate status reports
Identify risks
Create release notes
🏆 Evaluation Criteria
Practical usefulness (real problem solved)
Prompt quality (clarity and effectiveness)
Output quality (accuracy and usefulness)
Impact (time/effort saved)
🎁 Outcomes
Best prompts will be added to an internal AI Prompt Library
Top teams will be recognized and shortlisted for the next stage:
👉 AI in Action – Real Use Case Hackathon
